
What is context path ??
=======================
=> Project name we can use as context path 



====> Client can send data to server in below 3 ways
        1. Query Parameters
        2. Path Parameters 
        3. Request Body 


++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
      Query Parameters
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
=> Query Parameters are used to send data from client to server in URL..
=> Query Parameters also called as Requuest Parameters..
=> Query Parameters will represent data in key value format ..
=> Query Parameters should present only at end of the URL..
=> Query Parameters will start with " ? " symbol...
=> Query Parameters will be separated by " & " symbol..

Ex-1 : www.youtbe.com/watch?v=asf797979

---> v=asf797979 this part is called key value pair ...

=> To read Query Parameters in Spring Controller we will use @RequestParam annotation..
                                  
                                  ======================
                                      Path Parameters 
                                  ======================
=> Path Parameters are used  to send data from Client to server in URL..
=> Path Parameters are also called as URL parameters .

Note: Path Parameters will represent data directly (without keys ) like below 

Ex: www.ashokit.in/course/{cname}/trainer/{tname}

=> Path Parameters can present anywhere in the URL















































